NAME
	geo-fixture (service) - write and continuously rewrite a synthetic tree of ndb-stanza entity and feature files, advancing simulated units along fixed courses

INTERFACE
	service (MatrixService)

READS
	nothing - the mount parameter is unused; all data is generated
	in-process

WRITES	(to its outdir /tmp/matrix/geo-fixture/ - a consumer mounts it there)
	entities/<id>	ndb stanza, one key=value per line:
			id= lat= lon= affil= kind= label= course= speed=
			(five units, rewritten every tick)
	features/<id>	ndb stanza: id= type=(polygon|polyline|circle)
			points=<lat,lon ...> [radius=] color=RRGGBBAA
			[fill=] width= label= (written once at init)

DESCRIPTION
	1000 ms tick.  Dead-reckons unit positions from course and speed,
	wrapping within a fixed bounding box (San Francisco Bay).  The
	unit set exercises friend, hostile, neutral, and unknown
	affiliations and air/sea/ground kinds.  A data source for
	exercising ndb-stanza geo consumers without external feeds.

SEE ALSO
	geo-map (renders this output format)
